rofile"> her rank as Student Council President was taken away, the teachers and students have lost all respect for her, and her comfort food was taken away from her all because of the SSS's actions.</span> It's also sad when you realize that <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> Angel is a human like the rest of SSS and was just trying to fulfill her duties as Student Council President. Her reputation and life in the afterlife are ruined because she was trying to play by the rules.</span><ul><li> <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> Not that her past life as the <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/IllGirl" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/IllGirl">Ill Girl</a> Kanade Tachibana was much better.</span></li></ul></li><li> What about Yui? <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">In her past life, she was completely paralyzed and unable to do the cool things she saw on TV, hence her boundless energy.</span></li><li> Anyone who qualifies as a cutie in the SSS counts, given that <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> an unhappy life is a prerequisite to arrive in this afterlife</span>.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BreatherEpisode" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BreatherEpisode">Breather Episode</a>:<ul><li> Episode 4 is rather lighthearted compared to the drama-filled episode 3. Episode 8 piles on the <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BlackComedy" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BlackComedy">Black Comedy</a> just before <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> episode 9 shows us how Otonashi actually died</span>.</li><li> The OVA. <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LargeHam" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LargeHam">PREPARE THE HAM!</a></li></ul></li><li> 