and hope than he did, and that she had a purpose. He cuts his hair and applies for medical school.</span></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FaceDeathWithDignity" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FaceDeathWithDignity">Face Death with Dignity</a>: What the purgatory is trying to get the people who end up in it to do.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Facepalm" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Facepalm">Facepalm</a>: Otonashi does this in episode 10.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FateWorseThanDeath" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FateWorseThanDeath">Fate Worse than Death</a>:<ul><li> SSS believes that if you conform to the rules you may get reincarnated as lowly creatures like barnacles.</li><li> Also, Yuri's "punishment games". The only one we see, in the OVA, ends with <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> all of the SSS dead of dehydration</span>.</li><li> And now getting <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">assimilated by a Shadow NPC and being turned into an NPC</span>, thereby being stuck in that world forever.<div class="indent"><strong>Hinata</strong>: That's worse than death...</div></li><li> To put it more in perspective, <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">the SSS believes that NPCs have no souls. Therefore, being turned into one by a Shadow means that it has devoured your soul!</span></li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheFellowshipHasEnded" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheFellowshipHasEnded">The Fellowship Has Ended</a>: <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">When Yuri defeats the Shadows and most of the Battlefront has ascended, the remaining members hold a graduation ceremony before passing on themselves.</span></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/p